# Canvas Game

- This project uses React, TypeScript, Canvas, and Vitest.
- Game code lives under `src/game/`, organized by game module shards and testing helpers.
- Each directory under `src/game/` may contain at most one module: one implementation file, optional CSS, optional co-located test, and nested subdirectories for other modules. Multiple sibling implementation files in one folder must be split into module directories.
- Keep game logic testable by putting pure behavior in systems or small entities.
- Co-locate unit tests with the source area they cover.
- Prefer tests for pure logic over tests for canvas drawing details.
- Do not add dependencies unless the user explicitly asks.
- Keep constants local unless they are shared across three or more files.
- Preserve existing rendering and input behavior when changing physics, collision, or movement.
